Mix shrimp with Old Bay, garlic powder, tomato, green onion, olive oil and egg white in a medium bowl. Stir until well blended. Place bread slices on a baking sheet and broil until lightly toasted. Spread toasted slices lightly with mayonnaise. Spoon shrimp mixture evenly over bread slices. Bake at 350 degrees F 8-10 minutes, or until thoroughly heated and lightly browned.